# No Native Date

**NEVER use native `Date` or `Date.now()`.** Always use Luxon's `DateTime` for all date/time operations.

## Banned

```typescript
// ❌ All of these are banned
Date.now()
new Date()
new Date('2024-01-01')
Date.parse(str)
someDate.toISOString()
someDate.getTime()
```

## Use Instead

```typescript
import { DateTime } from 'luxon'

// Current timestamp (millis)
DateTime.now().toMillis()

// Current ISO string
DateTime.now().toISO()

// Current date
DateTime.now()

// Parse a date string
DateTime.fromISO('2024-01-01')

// Unix timestamp to DateTime
DateTime.fromMillis(timestamp)

// Comparisons
DateTime.now() > DateTime.fromISO(someDate)

// Formatting
DateTime.now().toFormat('yyyy-MM-dd')

// Relative time
DateTime.fromISO(date).toRelative() // "3 hours ago"
```

If you encounter existing `Date` / `Date.now()` usage, refactor it to Luxon when touching that code.
